M2.0.8 Light-client validator-set evolution â€” shared `validator_evolution` helpers

Extracts the four phases that mutate the active validator set inside
`mfn-consensus::apply_block` (equivocation slashing, liveness slashing,
bond ops, unbond settlements) into a new pure-helper module
`mfn-consensus::validator_evolution`, then teaches `mfn-light::LightChain`
to call those exact same helpers from `apply_block`. Result: light
clients now follow the Permawrite chain across arbitrary rotations
from a single genesis bootstrap, with byte-for-byte parity between
full-node and light-client validator-set transitions guaranteed by
construction (single source of truth).

Highlights:

- New `mfn-consensus::validator_evolution` module with four phase
  functions (`apply_equivocation_slashings`, `apply_liveness_evolution`,
  `apply_bond_ops_evolution`, `apply_unbond_settlements`), the
  `BondEpochCounters` shared-state struct, and a
  `finality_bitmap_from_header` extractor so light clients drive
  Phase B without re-decoding the producer proof.

- `mfn-consensus::block::apply_block` refactor: four inlined phases
  replaced with single-line calls. All 147 pre-existing unit tests +
  14 integration tests pass byte-for-byte unchanged â€” confirming
  semantic equivalence to the pre-refactor implementation.

- `mfn-light::LightChain` extension: tracks shadow state
  (`validator_stats`, `pending_unbonds`, `BondEpochCounters`,
  `bonding_params`) initialized in `from_genesis` to mirror
  `apply_genesis` byte-for-byte. New `apply_block` runs the four
  evolution phases on staging copies and atomically commits.

- New typed error `LightChainError::EvolutionFailed { height, index,
  message }` for the defense-in-depth Byzantine-quorum case.

- Extended `AppliedBlock` reports per-block validator-set deltas:
  `validators_added`, `validators_slashed_equivocation`,
  `validators_slashed_liveness`, `validators_unbond_settled`.

- The cross-block audit invariant: block N+1's header commits to the
  post-block-N validator set, so any drift between the light
  client's evolution and the full node's view is caught by the very
  next `apply_block` with `HeaderVerify { ValidatorRootMismatch }`.
  The chain's own headers audit the light client's evolution.

Tests: workspace 412 passing (147 mfn-consensus unit + 14
mfn-consensus integration + 22 mfn-light unit + 12 mfn-light
integration + others); +18 new tests for M2.0.8:

- 8 new mfn-consensus unit tests covering each phase's happy / edge
  cases.
- 8 new mfn-light unit tests covering shadow-state initialization,
  per-block stat advance, the cross-block drift detection, and the
  headline `validator_set_root` invariant.
- 2 new mfn-light integration tests: a real 5-block rotation chain
  (Register at block 1, Unbond at block 3, settlement at block 5)
  with `validator_set_root` agreement asserted after every block,
  and a tampered-bond-op rejection that fires at the
  `BondRootMismatch` body check before evolution runs.

Docs:

- New design note `docs/M2_LIGHT_VALIDATOR_EVOLUTION.md` covering
  the four-phase algorithm, the cross-block audit invariant, the
  full test matrix, atomicity semantics, and what's intentionally
  not in scope.
- Updated `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/CONSENSUS.md`,
  `docs/ROADMAP.md`, `mfn-consensus/README.md`, `mfn-light/README.md`,
  and the top-level `README.md` to reflect the new module, updated
  test counts (394 â†’ 412), and the milestone-shipped status.

- Regenerated `CODEBASE_STATS.md`.

What this unlocks: trustless long-running light clients (wallets,
dashboards, bridges, in-browser WASM clients) can now follow
Permawrite indefinitely from a single genesis bootstrap, with full
cryptographic verification at every step and no need to re-bootstrap
across rotations.
